media.altText:
pick yourself off the floor, child. you are not finished. 
you still have things to give, in the hollow of your mouth and under that thin skin. there is still gold upon your head and pearls within your gums. your spine still bends just so.
your ribcage has long since started blooming and you've yet petals to harvest from your spine. your heart is beating, and your lungs lay, torn, alive in the pit of you.
can't you see them move? take that breath. open that maw, and drink air from my palms. your shoulders are not worn to dust, and your feet still hold your weight.
the pillars are crumbling, dear thing. the skies are ripping at the seams. another red giant. another sunset. another layer of skin. 
you were made for this. don't be silly now. straighten your back and let me wipe all this mess from your dear face. look at me, soiling myself for you. was not this handkerchief once white? however will i get that stain out?
hold on, child. you are not finished.

media.altText:
Exercise and Stress Relief

Stress can impact our health and well-being negatively. Stress might happen in various situations e.g. when we are running late, before an interview, unexpected life changes, issues in relationships etc. In response to stress, our body releases the hormone cortisol, to prepare our body for a fight or flight response. Frequent stress can lead to many issues like anxiety & depression, irritability, high blood pressure, weight gain, sleep problems, heart attack or stroke.

To reduce the effects of stress, you can do physical exercise, as it releases "happy hormones". To keep your body and mind healthy include exercise in your daily life - whether it's going for walks, runs, doing strength exercise or brief intense workouts that suits your lifestyle.

media.altText:
Passive behavior can lead to a range of mental health challenges, including anxiety, depression, and low self-esteem. By avoiding conflict and suppressing your own feelings and desires, you may be putting the needs of others before your own and neglecting your own well-being.

Remember, it's important to prioritize your own needs and feelings, and to communicate assertively with others. Speak up, set boundaries, and prioritize your own mental health and wellness.

Transform Happily is here to support you on your journey towards assertiveness and self-advocacy. Our platform provides a range of resources and tools to help you improve your communication skills, build self-confidence, and prioritize your own mental health and wellness. Take the first step towards positive change by exploring our platform today.
